      "text": [
        ": سَأَلْتُهُ عَنِ اَلرَّجُلِ يَكُونُ خَلْفَ اَلْإِمَامِ فَيُطِيلُ اَلْإِمَامُ اَلتَّشَهُّدَ قَالَ «يُسَلِّمُ وَ يَمْضِي لِحَاجَتِهِ إِنْ أَحَبَّ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.1164 - Ubaydullah ibn Ali Al-Halabi narrated from Zurarah from Imam Jafar ibn Muhammad Al-Sadiq (as) who said:\nI asked him about a person who is behind the Imam, and the Imam prolongs the tashahhud (sitting for testimony).\nImam (as) said: \"He may perform the taslim (salutation of peace) and leave if he wishes.\""
        ]
      }
    },
